      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Of all the people in your article, the one who haunts me is Jeremy Leslie, the 3-year-old who had, perhaps, the least to say in the failed co-parenting arrangement.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Of all the people in your article, the one who haunts me is Jeremy Leslie, the 3-year-old who had, perhaps, the least to say in the failed co-parenting arrangement.</p>
        <p>We are told how Susan Leslie feels, how Evelyn Mirach feels and how her daughter, Christy, feels, but not one word is said of how Jeremy feels in the aftermath of a major upheaval in his life. The story seems incomplete without it. DIANE ASHACHIK Passaic, N.J.</p>
      </block>
